  "body": "## The problem\r\nhttps://docs.perl6.org/language/regexes#Literals\r\n\r\nif 'Life, the Universe and Everything' ~~ / and / {\r\n    say ~$/;           # OUTPUT: «and␤» \r\n    say $/.prematch;   # OUTPUT: «Life, the Universe␤» \r\n    say $/.postmatch;  # OUTPUT: « Everything␤» \r\n    say $/.from;        # OUTPUT: «19␤» \r\n    say $/.to;          # OUTPUT: «22␤» \r\n};\r\n\r\nREPL:\r\nif 'Life, the Universe and Everything' ~~ / and / { say '|' ~ ~$/ ~ '|'; say '|' ~ $/.prematch ~ '|'; say '|' ~ $/.postmatch ~ '|'; say $/.from; say $/.to; }\r\n|and|\r\n|Life, the Universe |\r\n| Everything|\r\n19\r\n22\r\n\r\n## Suggestions\r\n\r\n**Correction**: add a space after 'Universe' in the comment, which is critical due to the context of this section of the documentation.\r\n\r\nif 'Life, the Universe and Everything' ~~ / and / {\r\n    say ~$/;           # OUTPUT: «and␤» \r\n    say $/.prematch;   # OUTPUT: «Life, the Universe ␤»\r\n    say $/.postmatch;  # OUTPUT: « Everything␤» \r\n    say $/.from;        # OUTPUT: «19␤» \r\n    say $/.to;          # OUTPUT: «22␤» \r\n};",
